FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1778951200
OL,3,CMan jailed for killing 'beloved dad'
OL,4,Cwith punch outside Wetherspoon pub
OL,6,FOn Friday, Newport Crown Court heard
OL,7,FO'Callaghan approached Mr Carpenter
OL,8,Fand his friends at around midnight on
OL,9,Fthe evening in February this year,
OL,10,Fasking him "who are you then?" and
OL,11,Frequesting he follow him outside.
OL,13,FIt was in an alleyway outside the JD
OL,14,FWetherspoon pub that O'Callaghan twice
OL,15,Fstruck Mr Carpenter "unprovoked"
OL,16,Fbefore fleeing the scene.
OL,18,FMr Carpenter collapsed and later died
OL,19,Fin hospital, having suffered severe
OL,20,Fhead injuries as a result of the blow.
OL,26,@rD@LOUrD@^O]wD@UOUwD@`O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1778951200
OL,3,CMan jailed for killing 'beloved dad'
OL,4,Cwith punch outside Wetherspoon pub
OL,6,FThe court heard both Mr Carpenter and
OL,7,FO'Callaghan visited the Picture House
OL,8,Fon the evening of February 20 with
OL,9,Fseparate groups of friends.
OL,11,FJudge Daniel Williams said: "You
OL,12,Fheaded to the table where Marcus
OL,13,FCarpenter and his friends were, you
OL,14,Frecognised one of his friends from him
OL,15,Fworking in a pub in Tredegar.
OL,17,F"You then approached Marcus Carpenter
OL,18,Fand asked who he was ... You had heard
OL,19,Fthat Marcus Carpenter had been saying
OL,20,Fthings about you to other people.
OL,26,@sD@]OUyD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1778951200
OL,3,CMan jailed for killing 'beloved dad'
OL,4,Cwith punch outside Wetherspoon pub
OL,6,F"You are very quick to think that
OL,7,Fyou've been wronged by others,
OL,8,Fwhatever the truth of the situation."
OL,10,FNewport Crown Court heard there
OL,11,F"didn't appear to be any bad feeling"
OL,12,Fbetween the two men and Mr Carpenter
OL,13,Ffollowed O'Callaghan outside.
OL,15,FOnce outside O'Callaghan, who "felt
OL,16,Fdisrespected" by Mr Carpenter, struck
OL,17,Fhim in the face.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@eO]sD@AOUsD@eO]wD@_OUxD@MO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1778951200
OL,3,CMan jailed for killing 'beloved dad'
OL,4,Cwith punch outside Wetherspoon pub
OL,6,FJudge Williams said: "It was needless,
OL,7,Fyou continued to behave in an
OL,8,Foverbearing, aggressive and
OL,9,Fintimidating way towards Mr Carpenter,
OL,10,Fwho at no stage was hostile, let alone
OL,11,Faggressive, towards you.
OL,13,F"But you were determined to harm Mr
OL,14,FCarpenter, whatever he did, and
OL,15,Fhowever uninterested he was in
OL,16,Fengaging with you."
OL,18,FCCTV footage played to the court
OL,19,Fshowed the two men continuing to speak
OL,20,Ffor several minutes, before
OL,21,FO'Callaghan delivered a second punch.
OL,26,@nD@VOUuD@AOUxD@SO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1778951200
OL,3,CMan jailed for killing 'beloved dad'
OL,4,Cwith punch outside Wetherspoon pub
OL,6,FMr Carpenter had his arms at his side
OL,7,Fwhen O'Callaghan threw the "fatal,
OL,8,Fsickening blow" to his head.
OL,10,FThe court heard that, after Mr
OL,11,FCarpenter collapsed, O'Callaghan
OL,12,Fattempted to drag his body and slapped
OL,13,Fhim, before fleeing the scene.
OL,15,FO'Callaghan later told police he had
OL,16,Fbeen acting in "self-defence",
OL,17,Fclaiming Mr Carpenter had been
OL,18,Faggressive towards him.
OL,20,FJudge Williams said: "Your selfishness
OL,21,Fseems limitless.
OL,26,@oD@\OUpD@OO]xD@POUxD@]O]|D@VOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,464,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F463A1778951200
OL,3,CMan jailed for killing 'beloved dad'
OL,4,Cwith punch outside Wetherspoon pub
OL,6,F"You claimed at first to be acting in
OL,7,Fself defence ` it was, of course,
OL,8,Fnothing of the sort.
OL,10,F"Your actions have caused unimaginable
OL,11,Fgrief, loss and sadness."
OL,13,FPeter Donnison, defending, told the
OL,14,Fcourt there was "little that can be
OL,15,Fsaid" on behalf of O'Callaghan, who
OL,16,Fwas arrested while trying to climb out
OL,17,Fof the window of a property in Cardiff
OL,18,Fseveral days after the incident.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUsD@YO]vD@QOUwD@EO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/11
